        <div><h2>Our approach</h2>
            <h3>Integrating ChatGPT into our education system without affecting Academic integrity might be challenging but from our research these are the steps:</h3>
        <p><div>
           <ul>
            <li>Clear Guidelines: Create clear guidelines for ChatGPT use to both students and educators. These guidelines define the responsible and ethical application of AI tools in academic tasks. <br><br></li>
            <li>Educator Training: train Teachers/educators on AI integration and understand their role in guiding students on the appropriate use of ChatGPT. This includes distinguishing between supplementary support and plagiarism. <br><br></li>
            <li>Plagiarism Detection: Implement advanced plagiarism detection software, emphasizing that student's work should be original.<br><br></li>
            <li>Peer Collaboration: Promote peer learning and collaboration while making it clear that final submissions must be the independent work of each student.<br><br></li>
            <li>Ethical Agreements: Have academic integrity agreements that sets clear expectations and consequences for academic misconduct. <br><br></li>
            <li>Critical Thinking Focus: Make sure students understand the importance of critical thinking, problem-solving, and creativity in the learning process, while using ChatGPT as a supporting tool rather than using it for answers only. <br><br></li>
           </ul>
           By using these strategies combined with clear guidelines, ChatGPT can significantly enhance the educational experience while upholding academic integrity. Smith, J., & Johnson, A. (2022).
        </p>
        
